Provide an optional global console pattern for users who want simple setup without passing console through all builders.

## Background
Some users prefer global configuration for simplicity:
sqlmodel::set_global_console(SqlModelConsole::auto());

Then all sqlmodel operations automatically use this console.

This is an optional convenience - explicit console passing remains the primary pattern.

## Implementation Details

### File Modifications
crates/sqlmodel/src/console.rs (create)
crates/sqlmodel/src/lib.rs (add module)

### Global Console Storage
use std::sync::OnceLock;
use std::sync::Arc;

static GLOBAL_CONSOLE: OnceLock<Arc<SqlModelConsole>> = OnceLock::new();

/// Set the global console. Can only be called once.
pub fn set_global_console(console: SqlModelConsole) {
    let _ = GLOBAL_CONSOLE.set(Arc::new(console));
}

/// Get the global console if set.
pub fn global_console() -> Option<Arc<SqlModelConsole>> {
    GLOBAL_CONSOLE.get().cloned()
}

/// Initialize global console with auto-detection.
pub fn init_auto_console() {
    let _ = GLOBAL_CONSOLE.set(Arc::new(SqlModelConsole::auto()));
}

### Builder Integration
Modify builders to check global console:
impl SessionBuilder {
    pub fn build(self) -> Session {
        let console = self.console.or_else(global_console);
        // ... use console in session
    }
}

### Precedence Rules
1. Explicit console on builder (highest priority)
2. Global console (if set)
3. No console (no output)

### Thread Safety
- OnceLock ensures single initialization
- Arc<SqlModelConsole> allows safe sharing
- No mutable global state after initialization

### Environment-Based Initialization
Optional auto-init based on env:
#[cfg(feature = "console-auto-init")]
#[ctor::ctor]
fn auto_init_console() {
    if std::env::var("SQLMODEL_CONSOLE").is_ok() {
        init_auto_console();
    }
}

## Usage Examples

### Simple Global Setup
fn main() {
    sqlmodel::init_auto_console();

    // All sessions now have console output
    let session = Session::connect(url).await?;
}

### Custom Global Console
fn main() {
    let console = SqlModelConsole::builder()
        .theme(Theme::custom())
        .build();
    sqlmodel::set_global_console(console);
}

### Override Global
fn main() {
    sqlmodel::init_auto_console();

    // This session uses custom console, overriding global
    let custom = SqlModelConsole::builder().plain().build();
    let session = Session::builder()
        .with_console(custom)
        .connect(url).await?;
}

